Date: Thu, 7 May 1998 13:59:40 +1000
From: Roy Mason <Roy.Mason@dpif.tas.gov.au>

Further to Ross Tancreds comment, while trichinella may not have been
detected on the Australian mainland the parasite, as _Trichinella
pseudospiralis_, occurs in the Australian island state of Tasmania. In
Tasmania the infection occurs in native marsupial carnivores (e.g. the
Tasmania Devil). The parasite has been demonstrated to infect laboratory
rats and mice and also the native marsupial brush tailed possum.
--
Roy Mason
Animal Health Laboratory
Launceston, Tasmania.
Australia 7250
e-mail: Roy.Mason@dpif.tas.gov.au
