[Both are correct about hypervitaminosis A resulting from polar bear liver,
but I wouldn't expect an acute presentation. In the instance mentioned, the
autopsies did find evidence of trichinosis. But either way, one should be
cautious when consuming polar bears. And to misquote Mrs. Beeton, "First
catch your bear". - Mod.MHJ
